Text.Value: Replacing and Installing Batteries
• Open the battery door, turn the battery door cover fastener one quarter turn counterclockwise
• If present, remove and discard the old batteries
• To install batteries into the battery compartment
• Hold the radiacmeter horizontally
• Locate the four contact springs
• Locate the "+" and "-" polarity indicators
• Starting with the lower left corner move counterclockwise to insert the batteries
• Ensure all 4 batteries are correctly located and seated properly
• Close and fasten the battery door
• Verify that the battery door is latched

Pre-Operation Test Procedures

Change Batteries

  • Ensure that the UDR-14 is turned off.
  • If the unit is not turned off prior to battery removal, all stored data will be lost.
  • Open the battery door by turning the battery door cover fastener ¼ turn counterclockwise and swinging the door to the open position.
  • If present, remove and discard the old batteries in accordance with local SOP.
  • Hold the radiacmeter horizontally (parallel to the ground).
  • Look inside the battery compartment and locate the four contact springs.
  • Locate the "+" and "-" polarity indicators on the battery door seal.
  • Starting with the lower left corner and moving counterclockwise, insert the four AAA batteries, orientating each battery correctly, as shown by the polarity indicator.
  • Ensure that all 4 batteries are correctly located and seated by pressing lightly on each.
  • The batteries should move up and down freely and spring back when released.
  • Close and fasten the battery door by swinging it closed against the gasket, pressing the door against the gasket, and turning the fastener ¼ turn clockwise.
  • Verify that the battery door is latched.
  • The UDR-14 should display the word "SLEEP" on the LCD display.
Ensure that the Radiacmeter is turned off. If the unit is not turned off prior to battery removal, all stored data will be lost.
